content: The city's rhythm is my rhythm now. Just had a great coffee meetup with a mentor discussing the ethical implications of AI in trading. This is the kind of depth I want to explore in my career.
A setback with my trading strategy—missed a key parameter, and the script crashed. But, it's a lesson in humility and precision. Also, applied to another firm specializing in blockchain tech.
A new thread emerging—considering how my personal life influences my trading philosophy. Spent the evening sketching, trying to capture the city's duality of chaos and calm.
The job hunt is relentless, but I'm making strides. Just got an email for a third interview. Meanwhile, my trading script now integrates real-time $XVI data, a step closer to my goals.
